#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:2
msgid "Tornado 2.1 新特性"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:5
msgid "Sep 20, 2011"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:8
msgid "Backwards-incompatible changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:10
msgid ""
"Support for secure cookies written by pre-1.0 releases of Tornado has "
"been removed.  The `.RequestHandler.get_secure_cookie` method no longer "
"takes an ``include_name`` parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:13
msgid ""
"The ``debug`` application setting now causes stack traces to be displayed"
" in the browser on uncaught exceptions.  Since this may leak sensitive "
"information, debug mode is not recommended for public-facing servers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:18
msgid "Security fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:20
msgid ""
"Diginotar has been removed from the default CA certificates file used by "
"``SimpleAsyncHTTPClient``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:24
msgid "New modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:26
msgid ""
"`tornado.gen`:  A generator-based interface to simplify writing "
"asynchronous functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:28
msgid ""
"`tornado.netutil`:  Parts of `tornado.httpserver` have been extracted "
"into a new module for use with non-HTTP protocols."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:30
msgid ""
"`tornado.platform.twisted`:  A bridge between the Tornado IOLoop and the "
"Twisted Reactor, allowing code written for Twisted to be run on Tornado."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:32
msgid ""
"`tornado.process`:  Multi-process mode has been improved, and can now "
"restart crashed child processes.  A new entry point has been added at "
"`tornado.process.fork_processes`, although "
"``tornado.httpserver.HTTPServer.start`` is still supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:38
msgid "``tornado.web``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:40
msgid ""
"`tornado.web.RequestHandler.write_error` replaces ``get_error_html`` as "
"the preferred way to generate custom error pages (``get_error_html`` is "
"still supported, but deprecated)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:43
msgid ""
"In `tornado.web.Application`, handlers may be specified by (fully-"
"qualified) name instead of importing and passing the class object itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:46
msgid ""
"It is now possible to use a custom subclass of ``StaticFileHandler`` with"
" the ``static_handler_class`` application setting, and this subclass can "
"override the behavior of the ``static_url`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:49
msgid ""
"`~tornado.web.StaticFileHandler` subclasses can now override "
"``get_cache_time`` to customize cache control behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:51
msgid ""
"`tornado.web.RequestHandler.get_secure_cookie` now has a ``max_age_days``"
" parameter to allow applications to override the default one-month "
"expiration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:53
msgid ""
"`~tornado.web.RequestHandler.set_cookie` now accepts a ``max_age`` "
"keyword argument to set the ``max-age`` cookie attribute (note underscore"
" vs dash)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:55
msgid ""
"`tornado.web.RequestHandler.set_default_headers` may be overridden to set"
" headers in a way that does not get reset during error handling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:57
msgid ""
"`.RequestHandler.add_header` can now be used to set a header that can "
"appear multiple times in the response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:59
msgid "`.RequestHandler.flush` can now take a callback for flow control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:60
msgid "The ``application/json`` content type can now be gzipped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:61
msgid ""
"The cookie-signing functions are now accessible as static functions "
"``tornado.web.create_signed_value`` and "
"``tornado.web.decode_signed_value``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:65
msgid "``tornado.httpserver``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:67
msgid ""
"To facilitate some advanced multi-process scenarios, ``HTTPServer`` has a"
" new method ``add_sockets``, and socket-opening code is available "
"separately as `tornado.netutil.bind_sockets`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:70
msgid ""
"The ``cookies`` property is now available on "
"``tornado.httpserver.HTTPRequest`` (it is also available in its old "
"location as a property of `~tornado.web.RequestHandler`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:73
msgid ""
"``tornado.httpserver.HTTPServer.bind`` now takes a backlog argument with "
"the same meaning as ``socket.listen``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:75
msgid ""
"`~tornado.httpserver.HTTPServer` can now be run on a unix socket as well "
"as TCP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:77
msgid ""
"Fixed exception at startup when ``socket.AI_ADDRCONFIG`` is not "
"available, as on Windows XP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:81
msgid "``IOLoop`` and ``IOStream``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:83
msgid ""
"`~tornado.iostream.IOStream` performance has been improved, especially "
"for small synchronous requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:85
msgid ""
"New methods ``tornado.iostream.IOStream.read_until_close`` and "
"``tornado.iostream.IOStream.read_until_regex``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:87
msgid ""
"``IOStream.read_bytes`` and ``IOStream.read_until_close`` now take a "
"``streaming_callback`` argument to return data as it is received rather "
"than all at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:90
msgid ""
"`.IOLoop.add_timeout` now accepts `datetime.timedelta` objects in "
"addition to absolute timestamps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:92
msgid ""
"`~tornado.ioloop.PeriodicCallback` now sticks to the specified period "
"instead of creeping later due to accumulated errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:94
msgid ""
"`tornado.ioloop.IOLoop` and `tornado.httpclient.HTTPClient` now have "
"``close()`` methods that should be used in applications that create and "
"destroy many of these objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:97
msgid ""
"`.IOLoop.install` can now be used to use a custom subclass of IOLoop as "
"the singleton without monkey-patching."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:99
msgid ""
"`~tornado.iostream.IOStream` should now always call the close callback "
"instead of the connect callback on a connection error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:101
msgid ""
"The `.IOStream` close callback will no longer be called while there are "
"pending read callbacks that can be satisfied with buffered data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:106
msgid "``tornado.simple_httpclient``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:108
msgid ""
"Now supports client SSL certificates with the ``client_key`` and "
"``client_cert`` parameters to `tornado.httpclient.HTTPRequest`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:110
msgid "Now takes a maximum buffer size, to allow reading files larger than 100MB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:111
msgid "Now works with HTTP 1.0 servers that don't send a Content-Length header"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:112
msgid ""
"The ``allow_nonstandard_methods`` flag on HTTP client requests now "
"permits methods other than ``POST`` and ``PUT`` to contain bodies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:114
msgid ""
"Fixed file descriptor leaks and multiple callback invocations in "
"``SimpleAsyncHTTPClient``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:116
msgid "No longer consumes extra connection resources when following redirects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:117
msgid ""
"Now works with buggy web servers that separate headers with ``\\n`` "
"instead of ``\\r\\n\\r\\n``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:119
msgid "Now sets ``response.request_time`` correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:120
msgid "Connect timeouts now work correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:124
msgid "Other modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:126
msgid ""
"`tornado.auth.OpenIdMixin` now uses the correct realm when the callback "
"URI is on a different domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:128
msgid ""
"`tornado.autoreload` has a new command-line interface which can be used "
"to wrap any script.  This replaces the ``--autoreload`` argument to "
"`tornado.testing.main` and is more robust against syntax errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:131
msgid ""
"`tornado.autoreload.watch` can be used to watch files other than the "
"sources of imported modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:133
msgid ""
"``tornado.database.Connection`` has new variants of ``execute`` and "
"``executemany`` that return the number of rows affected instead of the "
"last inserted row id."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:136
msgid ""
"`tornado.locale.load_translations` now accepts any properly-formatted "
"locale name, not just those in the predefined ``LOCALE_NAMES`` list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:138
msgid ""
"`tornado.options.define` now takes a ``group`` parameter to group options"
" in ``--help`` output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:140
msgid ""
"Template loaders now take a ``namespace`` constructor argument to add "
"entries to the template namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:142
msgid ""
"`tornado.websocket` now supports the latest (\"hybi-10\") version of the "
"protocol (the old version, \"hixie-76\" is still supported; the correct "
"version is detected automatically)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:145
msgid "`tornado.websocket` now works on Python 3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:149
msgid "Bug fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:151
msgid ""
"Windows support has been improved.  Windows is still not an officially "
"supported platform, but the test suite now passes and "
"`tornado.autoreload` works."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:154
msgid "Uploading files whose names contain special characters will now work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:155
msgid ""
"Cookie values containing special characters are now properly quoted and "
"unquoted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:157
msgid "Multi-line headers are now supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:158
msgid ""
"Repeated Content-Length headers (which may be added by certain proxies) "
"are now supported in `.HTTPServer`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:160
msgid "Unicode string literals now work in template expressions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:161
msgid ""
"The template ``{% module %}`` directive now works even if applications "
"use a template variable named ``modules``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v2.1.0.rst:163
msgid "Requests with \"Expect: 100-continue\" now work on python 3"
msgstr ""

